
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ccamp-flexigrid-lambda-label-05.txt'>
    <title>"Generalized Labels for the Flexi-Grid in Lambda Switch Capable (LSC) Label Switching Routers", Adrian Farrel, Daniel King, Yao Li, Fatai Zhang</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ccamp-flexigrid-lambda-label-05.txt</link>
    <description>GMPLS supports the description of optical switching by identifying entries in fixed lists of switchable wavelengths (called grids) through the encoding of lambda labels.  Work within the ITU-T Study Group 15 has defined a finer granularity grid, and the facility to flexibly select different widths of spectrum from the grid.  This document defines a new GMPLS lambda label format to support this flexi-grid.  This document updates RFC 3471 and RFC 6205 by introducing a new label format.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-09-10T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
